<dl id="n40099b"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40099b">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40099b"> 99(b)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> hog in the / hamam</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">O dear my son, thou hast done even as the hog who entered the Hammam <font color="green">[public bath]</font> in company with the great; but after coming out he saw a stinking fosse a-flowing and went and therein wallowed. <small> Richard F. Burton, trans. <a name="RFBS" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#RFBS"><cite title="source">Supplemental Nights to the Book of the Thousand Nights and a Night with Notes Anthropological and Explanatory</cite></a> (n.d.) xvi.28</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c10003h" href="c10all.htm#c10003h">VI.C.10:003(h)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
